      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly traceable to the clinical endpoint of plasma free haemoglobin elevation above safe threshold.",
      "rationale": "NIH is used as the QoI and is the standard metric; however, the mapping from NIH to clinical plasma free haemoglobin threshold relies on a single published correlation with wide confidence bounds. Direct clinical traceability is not established for this specific pump geometry."
